I have created an entertainment Remote Control card using Lovelace picture elements.
I created the buttons on imagefu.com. Very easy. Basic buttons are 100 x 50 pixels. Used the standard Home Assistant color, #0099ff.
The remote combines Apple TV controls on the top, TV controls in the middle. Sound from the Bose sound system is included only using the volume up, down and mute commands. Each button is linked to a script which executes the (series of) commands. Especially useful for switching from TV to Apple TV to Sonos music system, which normally requires three remote controls and now only one Entertainment RC screen.
The button png's are stored in the /local/images_tvremote folder, which on hass.io is located in the config/www/ directory.

####################################################
### Entertainment remote control                 ###
####################################################
        
  - title: TV
    icon: mdi:television
    cards:
      - type: picture-elements
        image: /local/images_tvremote/background_white2.png
        elements:
